== Health Benefits ==
''Note: [[Health effects of hot springs|Effects]] are not guaranteed for all individuals.''

Benefits associated with sulfur springs include the following:

=== Indications ===
==== Bathing ====
* '''General indications:''' Chronic {{ill|skin diseases|en|Skin disease|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, chronic {{ill|gynecological disorders|en|Gynecological disorder|qq=draft|qq=draft}} , {{ill|cuts|en|Cut (wound)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} , and {{ill|diabetes|en|Diabetes mellitus|qq=draft|qq=draft}} .

* '''Hydrogen sulfide type:''' Effective for {{ill|hypertension|en|Hypertension|qq=draft|qq=draft}}<nowiki/>and {{ill|arteriosclerosis|en|Arteriosclerosis|qq=draft|qq=draft}}
.

==== Drinking ====
* Beneficial for diabetes, {{ill|gout|en|Gout|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|constipation|en|Constipation|qq=draft|qq=draft}} , and {{ill|diarrhea|en|Diarrhea|qq=draft|qq=draft}} .
=== Contraindications ===
==== Bathing ====
* '''General contraindications:''' Overly sensitive {{ill|skin|en|Human skin|qq=draft|qq=draft}}<nowiki/>or {{ill|mucous membranes|en|Mucous membrane|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, particularly in individuals with {{ill|photosensitivity|en|Photosensitivity|qq=draft|qq=draft}} .<ref>[https://www.env.go.jp/nature/onsen/pdf/pamph_full_en.pdf Onsen_ABC]</ref>
